Blocks.Text: Failure case 3: When the task has a simple shortcut solution
Even if there exist meaningful patterns in training data, the DNN may still not learn these concepts.
To be precise, if a classification task can be conducted with some shortcut solutions without requiring
the DNN to encode complex concepts, then the DNN probably converges to the shortcut solution.
The relative strength of all concepts
The DNN collapsed to a simple (linear) model without encoding interactions between different
image patches when the task had a simple shortcut solution.
